課程概述 Course Description
       講授基本人類肌肉活動與動作之關係，並探討如何應用於臨床訓練。 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    Upon completion of this course, the student will be:
familiar with the common terminology describing human motion,
able to understand the principles of kinetics and kinematics,
able to describe the basic components and their anatomical relationships of a specific joint motion, and
able to differentiate normal and abnormal movement and aware of the contributing factors of abnormal movement.    

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Course Introduction / Movement Terminology2Basic Units3Central Nerve System4Shoulder and Elbow5Peripheral Nerve System61st term Exam.7Interschool Activity Week8Forearm and Wrist9Hand 10Nerve Supply of Upper Limb11Lower Limb12Nerve Supply of Lower Limb132nd term Exam14Trunk15Sensory Background to Movement16Motor Control17Components and Skills183rd term Exam. 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


